The paper deals with the generation of synthetic iris images using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the impact of these synthetic images on iris recognition systems, which is a security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques for generating synthetic images also falls under multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new framework for generating synthetic iris images, which can be considered as an artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
